[h3 id=Boostingdownwards 
	" Boosting downwards
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Every unspin boosts Samus down 5px, so unspinnning every other frame give you an instant ~2.6px/frame velocity. So when falling less than 3 blocks distance and moving forwards isn't a concern, boosting downwards is faster than normally falling.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Here are a few uses:
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Fallthroughcrumbleblocksfaster 
	" Fall through crumble blocks faster 
	[img class=embedright src=/images/gameresources/metroidfusion/FusionDrop.gif 
	]img
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Falling through crumble blocks (as shown) involve distances less than 3 blocks, so boosting downwards through them is faster than normally falling.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Falldownwaterquicker 
	" Fall down water quicker
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"When falling in water, your downwards velocity is automatically set to 1.5px per frame, meaning boosting downwards is 1.75 times faster.
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Corollaxtrick 
	" Corollax trick
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"The Corollax trick is when you duck as soon as you hit the ground to store a shinespark after speed boosting off a ledge. You can also jump and do the Corollax trick. To do this you have to jump without spinning by pressing:
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Frame 1: Nothing
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Frame 2: Jump
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Frame 3: Jump + forward
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Holding forward until you duck.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Here are a few uses:
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=FightBOXfaster 
	" Fight BOX faster
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Speed boost to the wrecked room after super missiles, perform a jumping Corollax trick as far as possible, and run to the point where the ground starts rumbling 
	[a id=r1 
	]a
	[sup 
		"[
		[a href=#1 
			"1
		]a
		"]
	]sup
	", then spark back to the start of the room. (
	[a class=extlink href=http://dehacked.2y.net/microstorage.php/info/551257223/Pre-BOX%20spark.vbm rel=nofollow 
		"reference vbm
	]a
	")
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/P.JBoy 
		"P.JBoy
	]a
	": I've tried and failed sparking into box's room itself, if anyone else wants to have a go, 
	[a class=extlink href=http://dehacked.2y.net/microstorage.php/info/1772566797/Failed%20%286%20frames%29%20BOX%20Spark.vbm rel=nofollow 
		"here
	]a
	"'s my attempt.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=EngageNOCSA-Xfaster 
	" Engage NOC SA-X faster
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"In the energy tank room before the SA-X room, perform the jumping Corollax trick so that you land to the left of the energy tank, bomb the passage, grab the energy tank, travel the passage, shoot the door, and spark through. This only works if you grab the energy tank, because your shine timer stops while the bomb still explodes. (
	[a class=extlink href=http://dehacked.2y.net/microstorage.php/info/741956366/Pre-NOC%20SA-X%20spark.vbm rel=nofollow 
		"reference vbm
	]a
	")
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Gettingicemissilesbackwards 
	" Getting ice missiles backwards
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"After unlocking security level 3, go to the left edge of the room.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Run right 2 rooms. You should be able to run through the Kago and perform the jumping Corollax trick at the end of the ledge.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Run to the save room and spark into the right stairs. In the next room, perform the jumping Corollax trick again into the next room.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"In this room, spin jump far enough to the right (in order to avoid the wall above) and spark to the top. (
	[a class=extlink href=http://dehacked.2y.net/microstorage.php/info/203800349/Ice-missiles%20backwards.vbm rel=nofollow 
		"reference vbm
	]a
	")
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=SparkuptheARCshaft 
	" Spark up the ARC shaft
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"In the first ARC room, go to the left edge, run to the ARC shaft room, perform the jumping Corollax trick, go to the ladder, and spark up. (
	[a class=extlink href=http://dehacked.2y.net/microstorage.php/info/1513943241/ARC%20ladder%20spark.vbm rel=nofollow 
		"reference vbm
	]a
	")
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Spininmid-airandkeepjumping 
	" Spin in mid-air and keep jumping 
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"After doing a straight jump, you can spin without falling by pressing:
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[img class=embedleft src=/images/gameresources/metroidfusion/FusionSpin.gif 
	]img
	$LF
	"Frame 1: Backwards
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Frame 2: Jump + forwards 
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Powergrip 
	" Power grip
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"It's faster when gripping a wall to jump up instead of pulling yourself up, unless you're underwater without the gravity suit.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"It's also faster to pull yourself into a morphball tunnel than to enter in morphball.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"You can do 
	[a class=intlink href=/MetroidFusionTricks#spin_in_mid_air_and_keep_jumping_ 
		"Spin in mid-air and keep jumping
	]a
	" from a power grip as well.
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=JumpExtend 
	" Jump Extend
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"By coming out of spin or morphing/unmorphing, you reset all your vertical momentum (and horizontal momentum), so by doing this you take longer to fall and you can cover more horizontal distance.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Singlewall-jumping 
	" Single wall-jumping
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Taking the Jump Extend to the next level. By wall-jumping, morphing, moving towards the wall, unmorphing, moving towards the wall, morphing, etc. you will eventually reach the wall slightly higher up than where you started, allowing you to reach places unreachable by normal means. (see 
	[a class=extlink href=http://dehacked.2y.net/microstorage.php/info/1056025818/Power%20Bomb%20Tank%20TRO.vbm rel=nofollow 
		"here
	]a
	" for a vbm.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	(__wikiLink|/TODO|TODO)
	": Find the fastest way of performing this.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"This has a 2 main uses:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" Getting the missile tank after Mega-X.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Going through the top route after getting ice missiles.
		$LF
